<style>
/* Example CSS for Node-RED gauge to resemble a car gauge */

/* Target the gauge element */
.gauge11,.gauge12,.gauge13 {
/* Custom border style */
border: 10px solid #333; /* Dark border */
border-radius: 50%; /* Rounded shape */

/* Custom background color */
background-color: #ddd; /* Light gray background */

/* Optional: Add box-shadow for depth effect */
box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3); /* Soft shadow */

/* Custom font styles for the gauge value */
font-family: Arial, sans-serif; /* Use a readable font */
font-size: 24px; /* Adjust font size */
color: #333; /* Dark text color */
text-align: center; /* Center the text horizontally */
line-height: 1; /* Ensure text is vertically centered */
}
</style>
